/** \mainpage Floating-point Library  for Integer Processors (FLIP)

FLIP  is  a  C  library  for  software  support  of  single  precision
floating-point (FP) arithmetic on processors without FP hardware units
such as VLIW  or DSP processor cores for  embedded applications.  FLIP
provides   the   basic   five   operations:   addition,   subtraction,
multiplication, division  and square-root for  a quasi-fully compliant
single-precision  (SP)  IEEE 754  FP  arithmetic.   This library  also
provides some running modes  with relaxed characteristics: no denormal
numbers or restricted rounding modes for instance.

